&lt;h2 id="recent-projects"&gt;Recent Projects&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="project-card"&gt;
 &lt;div class="project-info"&gt;
 &lt;h3&gt;Social Robots&lt;/h3&gt;
 &lt;p&gt;The goal of this project is to design robots that interact with each other, with animals, and with humans. Rather than programming fixed outcomes, this project harnesses &lt;b&gt;emergence&lt;/b&gt; as a generative principle, engineering local interaction rules that give rise to &lt;i&gt;interesting, remarkable, and unusual&lt;/i&gt; (Olkowski, 2011) behaviors that transcend the predictable. &lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Robots</title><link>https://stxguy.github.io/robots/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://stxguy.github.io/robots/</guid><description>&lt;div class="robot-card"&gt;
 &lt;div class="robot-header"&gt;
 &lt;h2&gt;VICTOR&lt;/h2&gt;
 &lt;p class="robot-subtitle"&gt;Vibration Controlled Tactical Operating Robot&lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="robot-body"&gt;
 &lt;div class="robot-img"&gt;
 &lt;img src="https://stxguy.github.io/images/robots/VICTOR.jpg" alt="VICTOR"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="robot-info"&gt;
 &lt;p&gt;VICTOR is an inexpensive vibration-based robot that displays stochastic motion. It is used to study spontaneous self-assembly in teams of robots.&lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;div class="robot-links"&gt;
 &lt;a href="https://stxguy.github.io/files/victor_mechanics.pdf" class="robot-btn"&gt;⚙️ Mechanics CAD&lt;/a&gt;
